text.__SUMMARY__: Cyperus holoschoenus is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to Australia.The shortly rhizomatous perennial sedge typically grows to a height of 0.4 to 1.5 metres (1.3 to 4.9 ft) and has a tufted habit. The plant blooms between April and August producing green-brown flowers.In Western Australia it is found alongside creeks and rivers and in pools in the Kimberley region where it grows in sandy-clay soils.
